ZH: 我们经常去庙里祈福。
EN: We often go to the temple to pray for blessings.

ZH: 这座庙已经有几百年的历史了。
EN: This temple has a history of several hundred years.

ZH: 祖国的庙宇是华夏文明的重要遗产。
EN: The temples of the motherland are an important heritage of the Chinese civilization.

ZH: 庙前的大门上挂着一幅巨大的红灯笼。
EN: A large red lantern hangs on the gate in front of the temple.

ZH: 这个庙里供奉着许多神明。
EN: Many deities are enshrined in this temple.

ZH: 在庙宇里燃起了香火。
EN: Incense is lit in the temple.

ZH: 每年农历初一我们都要去庙里上香。
EN: Every year on the first day of the Lunar New Year, we go to the temple to burn incense.

ZH: 庙宇内的雕刻工艺非常精美。
EN: The carving craftsmanship inside the temple is very exquisite.

ZH: 每年春节庙会吸引了大量游客。
EN: The temple fair during the Spring Festival attracts a large number of visitors.

ZH: 许多人会在祈福后在庙里求签占卜。
EN: Many people will draw lots for divination in the temple after praying for blessings.

ZH: 寺庙是信徒虔诚祈福的地方。
EN: The temple is a place where believers pray devoutly for blessings.

ZH: 这间庙宇的建筑风格十分独特。
EN: The architectural style of this temple is very unique.

ZH: 庙宇内香火缭绕，令人心生敬仰。
EN: The temple is filled with incense, which is inspiring and admirable.

ZH: 今天我们要去参观古庙遗址。
EN: Today we are going to visit the site of an ancient temple.

ZH: 寺庙内的壁画描绘了历史故事。
EN: The murals inside the temple depict historical stories.

ZH: 穿过庙门，可以看到庄严的佛像。
EN: Passing through the temple gate, you can see the solemn Buddha statue.

ZH: 庙里的僧人在清晨起来诵经。
EN: The monks in the temple get up early in the morning to chant scriptures.

ZH: 这间古庙是当地文化遗产的重要组成部分。
EN: This ancient temple is an important part of the local cultural heritage.

ZH: 新年的第一天，人们都会去庙宇求个平安。
EN: On the first day of the New Year, people will go to the temple to pray for peace.

ZH: 这个庙会吸引了来自世界各地的游客。
EN: This temple fair attracts visitors from all over the world.
